fuller house is a historic home located at louisburg, franklin county, north carolina. it was built in 1856, and is a two-story, three bay by two bay, greek revival style frame dwelling. it has a hipped roof and rests on a low foundation of stone blocks. the front facade features a full width front porch. it was the home of noted poet and novelist edwin wiley fuller (1847â€“1876). it was listed on the national register of historic places in 1978. it is located in the louisburg historic district.